oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Travellers Rest located in Nashville, Tennessee.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Travellers Rest is the former home of Tennessee Supreme Court Judge John Overton. The home was first built in 1799, with several additions added during the nineteenth century. The site has also been spelled Traveler's Rest or Traveller's Rest.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Stairways; Porches; Balconies
